{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e84aea35-474c-4b99-95c5-865c40af9465","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you the general guidance for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC).\n\n## Changes needed\n\n### 1. **NuGet.org setup**\n- Go to your package on [nuget.org](https://nuget.org) → **Manage** → **Trusted publishers**\n- Add a **GitHub Actions** trusted publisher, specifying your repo owner, repo name, workflow file name, and optionally an environment\n\n### 2. **Workflow changes**\n\n**Add `id-token` permission** so the runner can request an OIDC token:\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # required for trusted publishing\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step.** Remove the API key usage:\n\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# AFTER\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nThe key change: **no `--api-key` flag**. The `dotnet` CLI (≥ 8.0.4xx SDK) automatically detects the OIDC token from the GitHub Actions environment when pushing to nuget.org.\n\n### 3. **Optional but recommended**: use a GitHub Environment\nLock it down with an environment (e.g., `nuget-publish`) with protection rules, and reference it in the trusted publisher config on nuget.org:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget-publish\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n```\n\n### 4. **Clean up**\n- Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo/org settings once verified.\n\n### Prerequisites\n- **.NET SDK ≥ 8.0.4xx** (the first version supporting OIDC for NuGet)\n- Package must already exist on nuget.org with trusted publisher configured, **or** you must configure it for new packages before the first push.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"51565623-05e5-43fa-b93e-9dbc19062951","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the working directory. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to trusted publishing (OIDC). Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":585,"requestId":"4C03:237CD0:619286C:6CCD965:69EC0F55"},"id":"44dfb644-e3b9-4e1c-9fba-6153024a25bf","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:48:34.586Z","parentId":"eaa8ae1d-d8a6-48bc-a32c-ff09b830daf6"}
